  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nEach type in `types` repeats a SSZ test for encoding then decoding the object.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/a1118e13ae1279d9bfcc7e4a9faff5a55da2507d/eth2/types/src/attestation.rs#L90-L99\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/a1118e13ae1279d9bfcc7e4a9faff5a55da2507d/eth2/types/src/deposit.rs#L65-L74\r\n\r\nThis is a prime target for a macro.\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\n- Create a `eth2/types/src/macros.rs` file to house the macro.\r\n- Create a `test_ssz_round_trip` macro, using the [slot and epoch ssz test macros](https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/a1118e13ae1279d9bfcc7e4a9faff5a55da2507d/eth2/types/src/slot_epoch_macros.rs#L548-L574) as inspiration.\r\n- Replace all the duplicated `fn test_ssz_round_trip(..)` tests with the new macro.\r\n",
